### ── Sample HTTP Requests (VS Code REST Client / IntelliJ HTTP Client) ──────

@base = http://localhost:8000

### 1. Process a prompt (cache miss → LLM call)
POST {{base}}/process
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": "user_alice",
  "prompt_id": "prompt_001",
  "text": "Explain quantum computing in simple terms",
  "priority": "high"
}

### 2. Same prompt again (should return cached: true)
POST {{base}}/process
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": "user_alice",
  "prompt_id": "prompt_002",
  "text": "Explain quantum computing in simple terms",
  "priority": "normal"
}

### 3. Idempotency — exact same prompt_id + text (returns existing result)
POST {{base}}/process
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": "user_alice",
  "prompt_id": "prompt_001",
  "text": "Explain quantum computing in simple terms",
  "priority": "high"
}

### 4. Conflict — same prompt_id but different text (expect 409)
POST {{base}}/process
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": "user_alice",
  "prompt_id": "prompt_001",
  "text": "Completely different text here",
  "priority": "normal"
}

### 5. Poll result by prompt_id
GET {{base}}/result/prompt_001

### 6. Low-priority prompt
POST {{base}}/process
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": "user_bob",
  "prompt_id": "prompt_low_001",
  "text": "Write a haiku about databases",
  "priority": "low"
}

### 7. Health check
GET {{base}}/health

### 8. Prometheus metrics
GET {{base}}/metrics

### 9. Validation error — empty text (expect 422)
POST {{base}}/process
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": "u1",
  "prompt_id": "p_bad",
  "text": "",
  "priority": "normal"
}

### 10. Validation error — invalid priority (expect 422)
POST {{base}}/process
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": "u1",
  "prompt_id": "p_bad2",
  "text": "valid text",
  "priority": "urgent"
}
